Australia defeated Pakistan by 39 runs to win a gripping struggle on the final day of the day-night first Test at the Gabba on Monday.Skipper Steve Smith ran out Yasir Shah for 33 to take the last wicket and end Pakistan&#8217;s brave effort to reel in a world record 490-run winning target.Pakistan looked on course to pull off an incredible victory on the back of Asad Shafiq&#8217;s knock of 137 but he was caught shortly before Yasir&#8217;s run out.-AFP